-- Sensitive Index Declines Most in a Week; Hindalco Shares Lead the Slide
-- B y   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 2010-12-23T06:36:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-23/sensitive-index-declines-most-in-a-week-hindalco-shares-lead-the-slide.html
India’s benchmark stock index
extended its drop to 0.3 percent. The Bombay Stock Exchange’s
Sensitive Index, or Sensex, lost 56.04 percent to 19,959.76 as
of 12:04 p.m. in Mumbai, set for its steepest decline a week.
Hindalco Industries Ltd., the biggest aluminum producer, fell
1.5 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
